pr_title: Added exit code for failure of tests
pr_body: This PR will give the exit codes for the failure of tests.In case of failure of any of the tests,it will exit and it indicates that the particular test has some error/bug in it while execution.

pr_title: Auto-toggle button for status of PRU
pr_body:
This PR adds auto-toggle button for the status of PRU.The status button syncs with the current status of the PRU and displays green highlight for on and red highlight for off.
This button is an auto-toggle button which does not need a manual click!

pr_title: Added column number in error message for precise error detection
pr_body:
This PR adds column number in error message for precise error location.
yylloc and %locations directive are used for getting the column number of error location.

pr_body:
This PR adds the compiler flags options during compilation with gcc-pru.
There are three compiler flag options -O1,-O2,-O3 which can be enabled in the command line interface.

pr_title: Added support for unary increment and decrement operators
pr_body: This PR adds support for unary increment and decrement operators(++,--) which can be used for much easier computation and programming in simpPRU.

pr_body:
This PR adds the support for return statements to be called anywhere in the function body,it removes the requirement that return statements needed to be called at the end of a function body only.
1.The return statements can be called only in function and not anywhere else.
2.Function body without return statements report an error

pr_title: Added the support of long long int (64 bit width) for integers
pr_body:
This PR fixes the error arising in hexadecimal computation which gives a 64 bit width over 32 bit width for input.The long long int strtoll() gives an edge over long int strtol() as it gives range of -2^63 to 2^63 – 1 over -2^31 to 2^31 – 1.
This resolves the error as it increases the range and gives the correct result with strtoll() function.
This PR adds the quit button feature in the simppru-console for exiting the console.
